Problem Statement:

Currently, master monitoring and testing plans are created manually at the beginning of each year using a checkbox trigger. This manual process is time-consuming, prone to delays if forgotten, and introduces unnecessary manual effort. We need to automate this process to ensure consistent and timely plan generation.

Technical Solution:

Automated Scheduled Generation:
Replace the manual checkbox trigger with a scheduled job (e.g., using a cron job or a scheduled task within the application) that triggers at the start of each year (e.g., January 1st).
Ensure the automated process leverages the existing template and logic used for the checkbox-triggered generation.
Restrict Manual Master Plan Creation:
Remove the checkbox trigger from the user interface.
Implement system logic to prevent the creation of new master plans through any other manual means after the automated process has run for the year.
Maintain the existing functionality for creating addendums to regional segments.
Ensure the existing addendum creation process is still reliant on a master plan existing for that year.
